===Etymology 2===
{{etymon|en|id=article|:inh|enm:a<id:article>|tree=1}}
From {{inh|en|enm|a}}, {{m|enm|an}}, from {{inh|en|ang|an|ān|one; a; lone; sole}}. More at {{m|en|one}}. The "n" was gradually lost before consonants in almost all dialects by the 15th century. Cognate with {{cog|gsw|a|t=a, an}}, {{cog|vmf|a|t=a, an}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|en|/eɪ/|a=stressed}}
** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Pvanp7-a (stressed).wav|a=UK,stressed}}
** {{audio|en|en-us-a-stressed.ogg|a=US,stressed}}
* {{IPA|en|/ə/|a=unstressed}}
** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Pvanp7-a (unstressed).wav|a=UK,unstressed}}
** {{audio|en|en-us-a-unstressed.ogg|a=US,unstressed}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪ|s=1}}<!--No ə rhyme: can't rhyme an unstressed word.-->
* {{homophones|en|eh|her|aa=non-rhotic,unstressed}}

