#* {{quote-book|en|author=David J. Bailey|title=The Storm|location=London|publisher=[[w:Austin Macauley Publishers|Austin Macauley Publishers Ltd.]]|year=2016|page=147|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781785548260/page/147/mode/1up|isbn=9781785548277|passage="There, I think that's done it," declared '''a''' triumphant John, "we just need to try it with the bar now, where is it?"}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2018|journal={{w|Associated Press}}|title=Rwandan court drops all charges against opposition figure|text="I will continue my campaign to fight for the rights of all Rwandans," '''a''' surprised but happy Rwigara told reporters after celebrating.}}
# Someone or something like; similar to; {{n-g|used before a [[proper noun#Noun|proper noun]] to create an example out of it}}.<ref name=OCD/>
#: {{ux|en|The center of the village was becoming '''a''' Times Square.}}
#: {{ux|en|The man is '''a''' regular Romeo.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Frederic V. Grunfeld|title=Rodin: A Biography|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:Henry Holt and Company|year=1987|page=88|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/rodinbiography00grun/page/88/mode/1up|isbn=0805002790|passage={{quote-gloss|Jules}} Pécher actually sculpted '''a''' sort of Statue of Liberty for the centerpiece of the monument, but for the rest he thought it advisable to call in Van Rasbourgh, and Rodin thus became a ghost sculptor to a ghost sculptor.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Ed Macy|title=Hellfire|location=London|publisher=w:Harper Press|year=2009|page=134|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/hellfire0000macy_b2w2/page/134/mode/1up|isbn=9780007288212|passage=Billy fancied himself as a bit of '''a''' Han Solo, but he shook his head. 'Stop being a wuss.' He grinned. 'Your go.'}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Laura Erickson|title=The Love Lives of Birds: Courting and Mating Rituals|location=North Adams, M.A.|publisher=w:Storey Publishing|year=2020|page=81|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/lovelivesofbirds0000eric/page/81/mode/1up|isbn=9781635862751|passage=For the first 5 or 6 days after the eggs hatch, the mother spends most of her time keeping the chicks warm while the father provides most of their meals. All that work may be what prompts the female to leave the family. They share feeding duties more equally during the next week or 10 days, until the young leave the nest. Producing a second batch is easier if she skips the last grueling week or two of provisioning fledglings. She can recharge her batteries by moseying off and, while on vacation, looking for '''a''' new Casanova.}}

=====Usage notes=====
{{mainapp|English articles#Indefinite articles}}
* In standard English, the article ''a'' is used before consonant sounds, while ''[[an]]'' is used before vowel sounds; for more, see [[an#Usage_notes|''the usage notes about an'']].

