===Etymology 3===
* From {{inh|en|enm|a}}, {{m|enm|o}}, from {{inh|en|ang|a-}}, {{m|ang|an}}, {{m|ang|on}}.
* Unstressed form of ''[[on]]''.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|en|/ə/}}
<!--No ə rhyme: can't rhyme an unstressed word.-->

====Preposition====
{{head|en|prepositions}}

# ''To do with separation;'' In, into. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{co|en|torn '''a''' pieces}}
# ''To do with time;'' Each, per, in, on, by. {{n-g|Often occurs between two nouns, where the first noun occurs at the end of a verbal phrase.}}{{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux|en|I brush my teeth twice '''a''' day.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet|IV|v|text='''A''' Sundays}}
#* {{quote-web|en|title=UN Study: China, US, Japan Lead World AI Development|url=https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/un-study-china-us-japan-lead-world-ai-development/4769094.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207184548/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/un-study-china-us-japan-lead-world-ai-development/4769094.html|archivedate=7 February 2019|work=w:Voice of America|date=3 February 2019|passage=Patent requests for machine learning activities grew on average by 28 percent '''a''' year between 2013 and 2016, the study found.}}
# ''To do with status;'' In. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* ''{{w|King James Bible}}'' (II Chronicles 2:18)
#*: To set the people '''a''' worke.
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with position or direction;'' In, on, at, by, towards, onto. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{co|en|stand '''a''' tiptoe}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with process, with a passive verb;'' In the course of, experiencing. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-song|en|year=1964|author=w:Bob Dylan|title=w:The Times They Are a-Changin'|passage=The times, they are '''a'''-changin'.}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with an action, an active verb;'' Engaged in. {{defdate|16th c.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Coriolanus|4|2|text=It was '''a''' doing.}}
#* {{RQ:KJV|Hebrews|11|21|text=Jacob, when he was '''a''' dying}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with an action/movement;'' To, into. {{defdate|16th c.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} ''To do with method;'' In, with. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Marlowe Jew of Malta|scene=iii|text=Stands here '''a''' purpose.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} ''To do with role or capacity;'' In. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{co|en|[[a God's name|'''a''' God’s name]]}}

=====Usage notes=====
* {{sense|position, direction}} Can also be attached without a hyphen, as [[aback]], [[ahorse]], [[afoot]]. See [[a-]]
* {{sense|separation}} Can also be attached without hyphen, as [[asunder]]. See [[a-]]
* {{sense|status}} Can also be attached without hyphen, as [[afloat]], [[awake]]. See [[a-]].
* {{sense|process}} Can also be attached with or without hyphen, as [[a-changing]]

