===Etymology 4===
From {{inh|en|enm|a}}, {{m|enm|ha}} contraction of {{m|enm|have}}, or {{m|enm|haven}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|en|'a}}, {{l|en|'a'}}, {{l|en|ha}}, {{l|en|ha'}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|en|/ə/}}
<!--No ə rhyme: can't rhyme an unstressed word.-->

====Verb====
{{head|en|verb forms}}

# {{senseid|en|have}} {{lb|en|dialectal|or|slang}} [[have#Verb|Have]] {{gl|auxiliary verb}}.
#: {{ux|en|I'd '''a''' come, if you'd '''a''' asked.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet Q1-2|act=IV|scene=v|sig=H2|page=56|passage=So would I '''a''' done, by yonder Sunne, / If thou hadſt not come to my bed.}}
#* {{RQ:Alcott Hospital Sketches|page=36|passage="Well, I reckon it did, marm, for that shot would '''a''' gone a couple a inches deeper but for my old mammy's camphor bag," answered the cheerful philosopher.}}
#* {{RQ:Twain Huckleberry Finn|page=54|passage=He dropped below me, with the current, and by-and-by he come a-swinging up shore in the easy water, and he went by so close I could '''a''' reached out the gun and touched him.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=Robert Hollan|chapter=A, ''prep.''|title=A Glossary of Words Used in the County of Chester|series=w:English Dialect Society|seriesvolume=XVI|location=London|publisher=w:Trübner & Co.|year=1886|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/aglossarywordsu01hollgoog/page/n18/mode/1up|passage=Oi'd '''a''' gen im a clout, if oi'd been theer.|brackets=on}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:John Ehle|title=w:The Land Breakers|location=New York, N.Y.{{nb...|Evanston, I.L.; London}}|publisher=w:Harper & Row, Publishers|year=1964|page=53|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/landbreakers00ehle/page/53/mode/1up|passage=They live in the river bottom. Don't you know a thing? I thought you must '''a''' seen them, since they was here all winter, cutting at the woods and burning brush.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:William Brodrick|title=The Discourtesy of Death|location=London|publisher=w:Little, Brown|year=2013|page=247|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/discourtesyofdea0000brod_l7c9/page/247/mode/1up|isbn=9781408704721|passage='I never told him, pleaded Liam. 'If I 'ad '''a''' done, he'd '''a''' taken the rifles, wouldn't he? Thing is, I wanted to fire a gun for real. See what it felt like. So I just borrowed it and went out on me own to have a go. But I didn't get the chance because I came across a patrol and I panicked and chucked the thing in a bin.'}}
# {{lb|en|dialectal|or|slang|rare}} [[had#Verb|had]] {{gl|auxiliary verb}}.
#* {{quote-journal|en|author={{w|Octave Thanet}} {{quote-gloss|pseudonym; Alice French}}|title=The Mortgage on Jeffy|magazine=w:Scribner's Magazine|number=4|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=w:Charles Scribner's Sons|month=October|year=1887|volume=II|page=478|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/sim_scribners-magazine_1887-10_2_4/page/478/mode/1up|column=1|issn=2152-792X|oclc=1590821|passage=I wisht you '''a''' seen 'im; fust he looked mighty gubious; then he begins ter laff. He'll git likened ter ridin' mighty briefly."}}

