==Breton==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|br|cel-bry-pro|*a}}, from {{inh|br|cel-pro|*au}}, from {{inh|br|ine-pro|*h₂ew}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|br|/a/}}

====Preposition====
{{head|br|prepositions}} {{q|triggers soft mutation}}

# [[from]] {{gloss|expresses origin}}
#: {{ux|br|tud '''a V'''rest|inline=1|people '''from''' Brest}}
# [[of]] {{gloss|indicates an amount}}
#: {{ux|br|un tamm brav '''a g'''ig|inline=1|a nice piece '''of''' meat}}
# of {{gloss|expresses a quality}}
#: {{ux|br|ur plac’h '''a''' enor|inline=1|a girl '''of''' honour}}
# {{n-g|after certain adjectives or adverbs expressing quantity}}
#: {{ux|br|ur voutailh leun '''a''' sistr|inline=1|a bottle full '''of''' cider}}
# {{n-g|after ordinal numbers with a plural noun}}
#: {{ux|br|tri '''a v'''ugale|inline=1|three children}}
# {{n-g|used in negative sentences with the grammatical object}}
#: {{ux|br|nʼem eus ket ken '''a v'''utun|inline=1|I donʼt have any more tobacco}}
# {{n-g|before the infinitive after certain verbs like [[paouez]], [[mirout]], [[diwall]], [[c'hwitañ]]}}
#: {{ux|br|paouezet eo ar glav '''a g'''ouezhañ|inline=1|it has stopped raining [lit. the rain has stopped falling]}}
# {{n-g|after substantivized adjectives used as nouns}}
#: {{ux|br|ur vrav '''a b'''lacʼh|inline=1|a pretty girl}}
# {{n-g|combined with a personal pronoun}}
#: {{ux|br|gwelet em boa '''acʼhanout'''|inline=1|I saw you}}
#: {{ux|br|an den a gomzan '''anezhañ'''|inline=1|the man Iʼm talking about}}

=====Inflection=====
{{br-prep-1|ac'han|anezh|type=a}}

===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|br|/a/}}

====Particle====
{{head|br|particles}} {{q|triggers soft mutation}}

# {{n-g|preverbal particle used when}}
## {{n-g|the subject precedes the verb}}
##: {{ux|br|ar mor '''a''' zo glas|inline=1|the sea is blue}}
## {{n-g|the object precedes the verb}}
##: {{ux|br|an den-se '''a g'''levan|inline=1|I hear that man}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|br|pronouns}} {{q|triggers soft mutation}}

# {{lb|br|relative}} that, which, who ''(used in 'direct' relative clauses, i.e. where the pronoun refers to the subject or the direct object of an inflected verb)''
#: {{ux|br|an hini '''a g'''aran|inline=1|the one '''whom''' I love}}

