==Catalan==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|ca|/a/}}
* {{rhymes|ca|a|s=1}}

====Letter====
{{head|ca|letter|lower case||upper case|A}}

# {{Latn-def|ca|letter|1}}

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|ca|no saber ni la a}}

=====See also=====
* [[Wiktionary:Catalan entry guidelines#Letters|see other Catalan letters]]

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|ca|la|ad}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|ca|/ə/|a=Eastern}}
* {{IPA|ca|/a/|a=Western}}

====Preposition====
{{head|ca|prepositions}}

# [[in]], [[at]]; indicating a particular time or place
#: {{ux|ca|Sóc '''a''' Barcelona.|I am '''in''' Barcelona.}}
# [[to]]; indicating movement towards a particular place
#: {{ux|ca|Vaig '''a''' Barcelona.|I'm going '''to''' Barcelona.}}
# [[to]]; indicating a target or indirect object
#: {{ux|ca|Escric una carta '''a''' la meva àvia.|I'm writing my grandmother a letter.}}
# [[per]]
# [[by]]
#: {{ux|ca|dia '''a''' dia.|day by day.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* When the preposition {{m|ca||a}} is followed by a masculine definite article, {{m|ca|el}} or {{m|ca|els}}, it is contracted with it to the forms {{m|ca|al}} and {{m|ca|als}} respectively. If {{m|ca||el}} would be elided to the form {{m|ca|l'|l’}} because it is before a word beginning with a vowel, the elision to {{lang|ca|[[a]] [[l’]]}} takes precedence over contracting to {{m|ca|al}}.

The same occurs with the [[salat]] article {{m|ca|es}}, to form {{m|ca|as}} except where {{m|ca||es}} would be elided to {{m|ca|s’}}.

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|ca|al}}
* {{l|ca|als}}
* {{l|ca|as}}
* {{l|ca|cap a}}
* {{l|ca|per a}}

