==Italian==

===Pronunciation===
{{it-pr|a*<r:DiPI><audio:It-a.ogg>}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{der|it|la|-}} {{m|la|a|ā|pos=''the name of the letter'' {{m|la|A}}}}.

====Letter====
{{it-letter}}

# {{Latn-def|it|letter|1|a}}

====Noun====
{{head|it|noun|g=f|cat2=indeclinable nouns|cat3=countable nouns|[[Appendix:Glossary#invariable|invariable]]}}

# {{Latn-def|it|name|A|a}}; {{l|en|a}}

=====See also=====
{{list:Latin script letter names/it/simple}}

===Etymology 2===
{{etymon|it|id=to|:inh|la:ad<id:to>}}
From {{inh|it|la|ad}}. In a few phrases, ''a'' stems from Latin {{m|la|ā}}, {{m|la|ab}}.<!--<ref>Angelo Prati, "Vocabolario Etimologico Italiano", Torino, 1951</ref>-->

====Preposition====
{{anchor|italian-preposition}}
{{head|it|prepositions}}

# {{n-g|Indicates the [[indirect object]].}} [[to]]
#: {{ux|it|Porta questo cesto '''a'''lla nonna.|Bring this basket '''to''' grandma.}}
#: {{ux|it|'''A'''i gatti piacciono i pesci.|Cats like fish.|lit=Fish are pleasable '''to''' cats.}}
#: {{ux|it|E lo chiedi '''a''' me?|You're asking that '''to''' me?}}
# {{n-g|Indicates the place, used in some contexts, in others {{m|it|in}} is used.}} [[in]], [[to]]
#: {{ux|it|Andiamo '''a''' casa?|Can we go home?|lit=Can we go '''to''' home?}}
#: {{ux|it|Ora sto '''a''' Palermo, '''a''' Roma ci torno domani.|I'm '''in''' Palermo now, I'll go back '''to''' Rome tomorrow.}}
# {{n-g|Denotes the manner.}} [[with]]
#: {{uxi|it|''[[appena]], [[a nuoto]], [[a piedi]], [[a caso]]|almost, swimming, by foot, randomly}}
# {{senseid|it|style}} {{n-g|Forms adverbs meaning {{m-g|in a manner related or resembling ~}}.}}
#: {{uxi|it|''[[a cappella]], [[a bestia]], [[a braccio]], [[a pennello]], etc.''}}
# {{n-g|Forms [[goodbye]] formulas from the time the persons will meet again.}} [[see you]]...
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''A''' domani!|'''Until''' tomorrow!}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''A''' dopo!|'''Until''' later!}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''A'''l prossimo Natale!|'''Until''' next Christmas!}}
# {{n-g|Introduces the ingredients of a dish, perfume, etc.}} [[with]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|pasta '''a'''ll'uovo|pasta '''with''' eggs}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|cornetto '''a'''l cioccolato|chocolate croissant}}
#: {{ux|it|inline=1|shampoo '''a'''l limone|lemon shampoo}}
#: {{ux|it|inline=1|patatine '''a'''lla pizza|pizza'''-flavoured''' crisps}}
# {{lb|it|CS}} {{n-g|Denotes the [[direct object]], but only if it's not preceded by articles}}
#: {{ux|it|Chiama '''a''' Paolo.|Call Paolo.}}
#: {{ux|it|E non ci avevi visto '''a''' noi?|And you didn't see us?|footer=the "us" here is repeated twice for emphasis}}
#: {{ux|it|Ascolti '''a''' me, signó!|Listen to me, ma'am!}}
# {{lb|it|followed by the definite article}} {{n-g|Forms an interjection that gives an instruction or calls attention to something.}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''Al''' ladro!|Thief!}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''Al''' fuoco!|Fire!}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''Al''' lupo!|[[cry wolf|Wolf]]!}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''All''''''attacco!|Attack!}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|'''All''''arrembaggio!|Assault! {{q|yelled by pirates}}}}
# {{lb|it|regional}} {{n-g|Forms [[continuous tense]] when preceded by {{m|it|stare}} and followed by verb [[infinitive]]s.}} [[-ing]]. {{n-g|The standard language for this scope uses [[gerund]]s.}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|che stai '''a''' di'?|what are you say'''ing'''?}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|it|stavo '''a''' dormi'|I was sleep'''ing'''}}
# {{n-g|Repeated indicates the amount by which something grows.}} [[by]]
#: {{uxi|it|'''a''' due '''a''' due|two '''by''' two; [[in pairs]]}}
#: {{uxi|it|[['''a''' poco '''a''' poco]]|[[little by little|little '''by''' little]]}}
# {{n-g|Indicates the [[agent]] of a verb in some contexts.}} [[by]]. {{n-g|Sometimes interchangeable with {{m|it|da}}.}}
#: {{ux|it|L'ho sentito dire '''a''' Livia.|I heard Livia say it.|lit=I heard it said '''by''' Livia.}}
#* {{quote-book|it|year=c. 1909|title=I vecchi e i giovani|author=w:Luigi Pirandello|chapter=2.3|text=Mi duole, creda, sinceramente, veder fare '''a''' un uomo come lei, per cui ho tanta stima, una figura... non bella, via! non bella.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* When followed by a word that begins with a vowel sound, the form {{m|it|ad}} can be used instead.
* When followed by the definite article, {{m-self|it|a}} combines with the article to produce the following combined forms:
: {|class="wikitable"
|-
