==Jamaican Creole==

===Etymology===
Compare {{cog|fr|c'est}}. {{rfe|jam}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|jam|/a/}}

===Preposition===
{{jam-prep}}

# Indicates location: [[at#Preposition|at]], [[in#Preposition|in]], [[on#Preposition|on]].
#: {{ux|jam|'''a''' mi yaad|'''at''' my home}}
# [[of#Preposition|of]]
#: {{ux|jam|Yunaitid Stiet '''a''' Amoerka|United States '''of''' America}}
# [[to#Preposition|to]]
#: {{ux|jam|Dem go '''a''' maakit. Mi a-go '''a''' skuul.|They go '''to''' the market. I'm going '''to''' school.}}

===Verb===
{{jam-verb}}

# to [[be]]
#: {{ux|jam|Jumieka '''a''' wahn ailan konchri.|Jamaica '''is''' an island country.}}
#: {{ux|jam|Wi '''a''' api.|We '''are''' happy.}}
#: {{ux|jam|Mi '''a''' di tiicha.|I '''am''' the teacher.}}
# {{n-g|As a [[copulative]] [[verb]]:}}
## {{lb|jam|with {{m|en|there}}, or {{m|en|it}}}} to [[exist]].
##: {{ux|jam|'''A''' tuu apruoch tu Ort sayans.|'''There are''' two approaches to Earth science.}}
# {{n-g|As an [[auxiliary verb]]:}}
## {{non-gloss|Used with present participles of verbs to form the [[continuous aspect]].}}

===Particle===
{{jam-part}}

# {{ng|Habitual present tense marker.}}
#: {{ux|jam|wan plies we dem '''a''' plie haki mach|a place where they play hockey matches}}
# {{ng|Precedes a verb to mark the -ing form.}}
#* {{quote-book|jam|year=1968|author=Beryl Loftman Bailey|title=Jamaican Creole Language Course: (for English Speaking Students)
|text=Jan sidong de '''a laaf'''.<br />Sta Kiet op de-'''a baal'''|t=John sat there '''laughing'''<br />Sister Kate is up there '''crying'''}}

===See also===
* {{l|jam|a-go}}

===Further reading===
* {{R:jam:majstro.com}}
* [https://opengrammar.github.io/jam/ A Learner’s Grammar of Jamaican, The Open Grammar Project]

