==North Frisian==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|frr|[a]|qq=short vowel}}
* {{IPA|frr|[aː]|a2=Sylt|[oː]|qq=long vowel, spelt ''aa''}}

====Letter====
{{head|frr|letter|lower case||upper case|A}}

# {{Latn-def|frr|letter|indef=1}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Sylt Frisian ⟨{{l|frr||aa}}⟩ was originally {{IPAchar|[ɔː]}}, but has since merged with ⟨{{l|frr|o|oo}}⟩. The letter ⟨{{l|frr|ā}}⟩ is used for {{IPAchar|[aː]}}. The diphthongs ⟨{{l|frr||ai, ia}}⟩ are both monophthongized to {{IPAchar|[ɛː]}} when followed by ⟨{{l|frr|r}}⟩.
* In Föhr-Amrum Frisian, ⟨{{l|frr||ai}}⟩ represents a lengthened diphthong {{IPAchar|[aːɪ̯]}} as if written ⟨{{l|frr||*aai}}⟩. The short equivalent is ⟨{{l|frr|e|ei}}⟩.

=====See also=====
* {{sense|North Frisian letters}} {{l|frr|[[a]], [[ä]], [[å]], [[ā]], [[b]], [[c]], [[d]], [[đ]], [[e]], [[ē]], [[f]], [[g]], [[h]], [[i]], [[j]], [[k]], [[l]], [[m]], [[n]], [[o]], [[ö]], [[p]], [[r]], [[s]], [[t]], [[u]], [[ü]], [[v]], [[w]] ([[q]], [[x]], [[y]], [[z]])}}

===Etymology 2===

====Article====
{{head|frr|article}}

# {{lb|frr|Föhr-Amrum}} [[the]] {{q|masculine and all-gender plural definite article, reduced form}}
#: {{coordinate terms|frr|q=full forms|de|dön}}

=====Usage notes=====
* For the alternative use of the form {{m|frr||a}} with certain original feminines, see {{m|frr|at}}.

