==Norwegian Bokmål==
[[Image:Latin letter A.svg|250px|thumb|The [[letter]]  '''''a''''' from the [[Norwegian]] alphabet.]]

===Etymology 1===
From {{der|nb|la|a}}, from {{der|nb|grc|-}} {{m|grc|Α||alpha}}, likely through the {{der|nb|ett|-}} language, from {{der|nb|phn|-}} {{m|phn|𐤀}}, from Proto-Canaanite [[Image:Protoalef.svg|20px]], from Proto-Sinaitic [[Image:Proto-semiticA-01.svg|20px]], from {{der|nb|egy|-}} {{m|egy|𓃾}}, representing the head of an [[ox]].

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|nb|/ɑː/}}
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|nb|/ɑː/|/a/|[æ]|q3=before u or in some Enɡlish loan words}}
* {{audio|nb|Pronunciation of Norwegian Bokmål «A», «a».ogg}}
* {{audio|nb|NB - Pronunciation of Norwegian Bokmål «a (fransk)».ogg}}
* {{hyphenation|nb|a}}
* {{homophones|nb|A|à|A-|a-|ah}}

