{{head|nb|interjections}}

# {{n-g|expression of [[surprise]] or [[horror]]}}
#: {{ux|nb|a, for noe tøv!|oh, such nonsense!}}
#* {{quote-book|nb|year=1888|author=Herman Colditz|title=Kjærka, et Atélierinteriør|passage=a, det er bare noe drit til han terracottaen|t=oh, that is just some crap for that terracotta guy}}
# {{n-g|expression of [[admiration]] or [[happiness]]}}
#: {{ux|nb|a, det gjorde godt!|oh, that felt good!}}
#* {{quote-book|nb|year=1897|author={{w|Fridtjof Nansen}}|title=Fram over Polhavet I|page=345|passage=a, kunde vi bare gi «Fram» slige vinger|t=oh, if only we could give "Fram" wings like that}}
# {{n-g|used with the words yes and no to give a sense of [[impatience]] or [[rejection]]}}
#: {{ux|nb|a jo, men hold nå fred!|oh yes, but keep quiet now}}
#* {{quote-book|nb|year=1874|author={{w|Henrik Ibsen}}|title=Fru Inger til Østråt|page=99|passage=a nej, det kan være det samme|t=oh no, it does not matter}}
