===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|nup|/à/}}

====Particle====
{{head|nup|particles|head=à}}

# [[not]] {{gloss|placed at the end of a clause to negate it}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|nup|Mi de eshìgi '''à''', mi ma de dàǹgi '''à'''.|I do'''n't''' have a dog, and I do'''n't''' have a cat.}}

===Etymology 3===
{{clipping|nup|lá}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|nup|/á/}}

====Particle====
{{head|nup|particles|head=á}}

# {{n-g|Marks the [[perfective]] aspect, for actions that are completed}}

=====Usage notes=====
'''á''', which is derived from the verb {{m|nup|la|lá|to take}}, functions like a verb so that the {{w|word order}} in the {{w|present perfect}} tense is that of a {{w|serial verb construction}}.

* {{ux|inline=1|nup|Musa shi dùkùn|Musa bought a pot}}
* {{ux|inline=1|nup|Musa '''á''' dùkùn shi.|Musa '''has''' bought a pot.|lit=Musa '''took''' a pot to buy}}

===Etymology 4===
{{clipping|nup|gà}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|nup|/à/}}

====Particle====
{{head|nup|particles|head=à}}

# {{n-g|Used to express the [[future]] tense}} {{gloss|placed before verbs}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|nup|A '''à''' lá èbi be nakàn|They '''will''' use a knife to cut the meat}}

