==Serbo-Croatian==

===Pronunciation===
* {{sh-IPA|a}}

===Etymology 1===
See [[#Translingual|Translingual section]].

====Letter====
{{head|sh|letter|lower case||upper case|A}}

# The 1st letter of the Serbo-Croatian Latin alphabet ([[gajica]]), followed by {{l|sh|b}}.

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|sh|sla-pro|*a||and, but}}.

====Conjunction====
{{sh-con}}

# [[but]], [[and]] (compare {{m|sh|ali|ȁli}})
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Učio sam c(ij)elo posl(ij)epodne, a ništa nisam naučio.|I studied for the whole afternoon, but I didn't learn anything.}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|A kako biste vi to napravili?|And how would you do that?}}
# [[while]] (on the contrary), [[whereas]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Stolovi su crveni, a stolice su zelene.|The tables are red, whereas the chairs are green.}}
# {{q|with {{l|sh|[[da]] [[ne]]}}}} [[without]] (usually after negative verbs)
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Ne mogu se uključiti u raspravu, a da ne napravim nered.|I cannot enter a discussion without making a mess.}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Odlazi, a da nije rekao ni zbogom.|He's leaving without even saying goodbye.}}
# ({{m|sh|a [[ȉpāk]]}}) [[and]] [[yet]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Pravi prijatelj zna sve o tebi, a ipak te voli.|The real friend knows everything about you, and yet he loves you.}}
# ({{m|sh|a [[kȁmoli]]}}) not to mention, [[let alone]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|U moru loših v(ij)esti teško je ostati objektivan, a kamoli optimističan.|In the sea of bad news it's hard to stay objective, let alone optimistic.}}
# ({{m|sh|a + [[i]] + [[da]]}}) [[even if]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|A i da jesam to napravio, ne bi to učinilo neku razliku.|Even if I did it, it wouldn't have made much of a difference.}}
# ({{m|sh|a + [[i]]}}) and [[so]], and [[also]], and [[too]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Sviđaju mi se plavuše, a i ja se pokojoj svidim.|I like blondes, and some of them even like me.}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|sh|Bili su žalosni, a i ja sam.|They were sad, and so am I.}}

===Etymology 3===
Attested since the 15th century. Probably of onomatopoeic origin. Compare {{cog|sl|a}}, {{cog|ru|а}}, {{cog|lt|o|õ}}, {{cog|la|o|ō}} and {{cog|grc|ὦ}}. These could all derive from Proto-Indo-European interjection {{m|ine-pro||*ō|oh, ah}}, but each form in individual languages could easily be an independent, expressive formation.

====Interjection====
{{head|sh|interjections|Cyrillic spelling|а}}

