===Etymology 1===

====Letter====
{{head|es|letter|lower case||upper case|A}}

# {{Latn-def|es|letter|1}}

====Noun====
{{es-noun|f|aes}}

# {{n-g|Name of the letter {{m|es|A}}.}}

=====Usage notes=====
Nominally, ''a'' always takes the usual feminine articles {{m|es|la}} and {{m|es|una}} (''la a'', ''una a''). This makes it an exception to the rule according to which feminine nouns beginning with stressed {{ic|/ˈa/}} frequently take the articles {{m|es|el}} and {{m|es|un}} otherwise reserved for masculine nouns (e.g., ''el {{l|es|alma}}'', ''un {{l|es|alma}}'').

=====See also=====
{{list:Latin script letter names/es/simple}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|es|la|ad||to}}.

