==Welsh==

===Etymology 1===

====Alternative forms====
* {{alt|cy|à||unpredictably short}}
* {{alt|cy|á||unusually stressed}}
* {{alt|cy|â||unpredictably or unusually stressed long}}
* {{alt|cy|ä||indicating disyllaicity}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|cy|/aː/}}
* {{rhymes|cy|aː|s=1}}

====Letter====
{{head|cy|letter|lower case||upper case|A}}

# {{Latn-def|cy|letter|1|a}} {{n-g|followed by {{m|cy|b}}}}

=====Mutation=====
* a cannot be mutated but, being a vowel, does take {{l|en|h-prothesis}}, for example with the word {{m|cy|afal||apple}}:
{{cy-mut|afal}}

=====Derived terms=====
* Digraph sequences: {{l|cy|ae}}, {{l|cy|ai}}, {{l|cy|au}}, {{l|cy|aw}}, {{l|cy|ay}}

=====See also=====
* [[WT:ACY#Alphabetization|Other Welsh letters and their names]]

====Noun====
{{cy-noun|f|âu}}

# {{Latn-def|cy|name|A|a}}

=====Mutation=====
{{cy-mut}}

===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|cy|/aː/}}
* {{rhymes|cy|aː|s=1}}

====Verb====
{{head|cy|verb form}}

# {{lb|cy|colloquial}} {{inflection of|cy|mynd||1|s|futr}}

=====Synonyms=====
* {{l|cy|af}} {{q|literary}}

===Etymology 3===
From {{inh|cy|owl|a|a(c)}}, from {{inh|cy|cel-bry-pro|*(h)a}}, from {{inh|cy|ine-pro|*[[h₂éd]]-[[gʰe]]}} (compare {{cog|cy|ag}} and {{cog|kw|ha}}).

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|cy|/a/}}
* {{rhymes|cy|a|s=1}}

====Conjunction====
{{head|cy|conjunction|triggers aspirate mutation (but not always in colloquial language)}}

# [[and]]

=====Synonyms=====
* {{l|cy|ac}} {{q|used before a vowel}}

===Etymology 4===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|cy|/a/}}
* {{rhymes|cy|a|s=1}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|cy|pronoun|triggers soft mutation}}

# {{lb|cy|relative}} that, which, who
#: {{uxi|cy|y dyn '''a w'''elais i|the man '''whom''' I saw}}

=====Usage notes=====
* ''a'' is used in direct relative clauses, i.e. where the pronoun refers to the subject or the direct object of an inflected verb (as opposed to a periphrastic construction with {{m|cy|bod|t=to be}}.
* ''a'' is not used with the third person singular present of the verb {{m|cy|bod}}, where the relative verb form {{m|cy|sydd}} is used instead:
*: {{uxi|cy|Mae'r dyn yn ifanc.|The man is young.}}
*: {{uxi|cy|y dyn '''sydd''' yn ifanc|the man who is young|qq=not {{m|cy||*y dyn '''a''' yw'n ifanc}}}}
* ''a'' is not used in indirect relative clauses, where the pronoun is part of a genitive or periphrastic construction. Instead the second relative pronoun {{m|cy|y|id=particle}} is used:
*: {{uxi|cy|Roedd chwaer y dyn yma.|The man's sister was here.}}
*: {{uxi|cy|y dyn '''yr''' oedd ei chwaer yma|the man whose sister was here|qq=not {{m|cy||*y dyn '''a''' oedd ei chwaer yma}}}}

