===Determiner===
{{head|yol|determiner}}

# [[the]], in later times '''''the'''''.
#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=THE WEDDEEN O BALLYMORE|number=3|page=94|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Maade '''a''' nicest coolecannan that e'er ye did zee.|translation=Made '''the''' nicest coolecannan that ever you did see.}}
#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=SONG|number=4|page=108|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage='''A''' vursth stroke hea strooke|translation='''The''' first stroke he struck}}
#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|page=110|chapter=JAMEEN QOUGEELY EE-PEALTHE|line=5-6|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=If ich hadh Peeougheen '''a''' Buch, Meyleare '''a''' Slut, Peedher Ghiel-laaune, an Jackeen Bugaaune,|translation=If I had Hugh '''the''' Buck, Meyler '''the''' Sloven, Peter the Smart Man, and John Boggan,}}

