==Yoruba==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|yo|/a/}}
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|yo|/á/}}

====Letter====
{{head|yo|letter|lower case||upper case|A}}

# {{Latn-def|yo|letter|1|á}}

====Noun====
{{head|yo|noun|head=á}} <!-- {{yo-pos|noun|á}} -->

# {{Latn-def|yo|name|A|a}}

====See also====
* {{see-temp|list:Latin script letters/yo}}
* {{see-temp|list:Latin script letter names/yo}}

===Etymology 2===
Likely a {{clipping|yo|àwa|t=we (emphatic pronoun)|nocap=1}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|yo|/ā/}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|yo|pronouns|head=a}} <!-- {{yo-pos|pronoun|a}} -->

# [[we]] {{gloss|first-person plural personal subject pronoun}}
#: {{ux|yo|Ó yẹ kí '''a''' dọ̀bálẹ̀ fún áwọn àgbàlagbà tí '''a''' máa ń pàdé.|It's necessary that '''we''' prostrate for elders that '''we''' meet.}}
#: {{ux|yo|'''A''' à tí ì rí wọn lónìí, ṣùgbọ́n '''a''' máa lọ sí báńkì lọ́la láti bá wọn sọ̀rọ̀.|'''We''' haven't seen them yet today, but '''we''''ll go to the bank tomorrow to talk to them.}}

=====Usage notes=====
Similar to other shortened subject pronouns, its usage is restricted and can only be found directly before a verb or pre-verbal marker. It cannot be used with particles/discourse markers such as {{m|yo|ńkọ́}} or conjunctions such as {{m|yo|àti}}, {{m|yo|pẹ̀lú}}, and {{m|yo|tàbí}}. In those cases, {{m|yo|àwa}} must be used instead.

===Etymology 3===

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense|mid-tone}} {{IPA|yo|/ā/}}
* {{sense|high-tone}} {{IPA|yo|/á/}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|yo|pronouns|head=a}} <!-- {{yo-pos|pronoun|a}} -->

# [[him]], [[her]], [[it]] {{gloss|third-person singular non-honorific object pronoun following a [[monosyllabic]] verb with a high-tone /a/}}
#: {{syn|yo|wọn<q:honorific>}}
#: {{ux|yo|Àá bá '''a''' sọ̀rọ̀ l'ọ́sẹ̀ t'ó ń bọ̀.|We'll talk to '''him''' next week.}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|yo|pronouns|head=á}} <!-- {{yo-pos|pronoun|á}} -->

# [[him]], [[her]], [[it]] {{gloss|third-person singular non-honorific object pronoun following a [[monosyllabic]] verb with a low- or mid-tone /a/}}
#: {{syn|yo|wọn<q:honorific>}}
#: {{uxi|yo|Wọ́n ti pa '''á''' o!|They've killed '''her'''!}}
#: {{uxi|yo|Ǹj'ó o kà '''á'''?|Did you read '''it'''?}}

====See also====
{{see-temp|yo-personal pronouns}}

